        "title": "test: fold HTTP API script proof into QA Lab",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Fold the OpenAI-compatible chat tools, OpenAI web_search minimal, native web_search assertion, and OpenWebUI probe script tests into QA Lab native evidence paths.\n- Add QA scenario YAML entries for the folded HTTP/API proof so taxonomy coverage fulfills `gateway.tool-invocation-api`, `gateway.openai-compatible-apis`, `runtime.reasoning-and-cache-controls`, `web-search.openai-native-web-search`, and `plugins.web-search-and-fetch`.\n- Update changed-test routing so edits to the existing Docker/client scripts run the new QA Lab evidence files.\n- Trim script-era cruft from the folded QA Lab tests while keeping behavior-oriented auth and HTTP API assertions.\n- Keep native Vitest evidence out of runtime parity tier selection so runtime-pair lanes only select flow scenarios.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openai-compatible-chat-tools.e2e.test.ts test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openai-web-search-minimal.e2e.test.ts test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openai-web-search-minimal-assertions.e2e.test.ts test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openwebui-probe.e2e.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/scenario-catalog.test.ts test/scripts/test-projects.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-node.mjs qa coverage --json --output /tmp/openclaw-qa-coverage-main-rebase-fix.json`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 qa/scenarios/runtime/openai-compatible-chat-tools.yaml qa/scenarios/runtime/openai-web-search-minimal.yaml qa/scenarios/runtime/openai-web-search-native-assertions.yaml qa/scenarios/runtime/openwebui-openai-compatible.yaml test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openai-compatible-chat-tools.e2e.test.ts test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openai-web-search-minimal.e2e.test.ts test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openai-web-search-minimal-assertions.e2e.test.ts test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openwebui-probe.e2e.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/scenario-catalog.test.ts test/scripts/test-projects.test.ts scripts/test-projects.test-support.mjs`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: HTTP/API script proof is now represented as QA Lab scenario evidence with primary taxonomy IDs instead of only living under `test/scripts`.\n\nReal environment tested: Local source checkout on this branch.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Focused Vitest command listed above, QA coverage report command listed above, oxfmt check, whitespace check, and branch autoreview.\n\nEvidence after fix: QA coverage report returned 126 scenarios, 172 coverage IDs, 106 primary coverage IDs, and 0 scorecard `*-not-found` issues. The target dotted IDs `gateway.tool-invocation-api`, `gateway.openai-compatible-apis`, `runtime.reasoning-and-cache-controls`, `web-search.openai-native-web-search`, and `plugins.web-search-and-fetch` are fulfilled.\n\nObserved result after fix: Focused tests passed across tooling, e2e, and extension-qa Vitest shards; autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\n\nWhat was not tested: The live Docker lanes `test:docker:openai-chat-tools`, `test:docker:openai-web-search-minimal`, and `test:docker:openwebui` were not run locally.\n",
